d at the center of the coming philosophy, Kishik points to some of the most promising directions that this philosophy can take.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477838140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804778381423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804778381.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles